HEADWORD: Chinse
<hw>Chinse</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Chinsed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Chinsing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To
thrust oakum into (seams or chinks) with a chisel , the point of a
knife, or a chinsing iron; to calk slightly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Chinsing iron</b></col>, <cd>a light calking
